    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Guardrail — Intent Classifier\n\nGPT-4.1-nano checks if the user input is a valid post generation/scheduling request. Returns `relevant: true/false`.\n\n**Passes:** Post requests, even if mixed with casual chat.\n**Blocks:** Greetings, random questions, off-topic messages.\n\nPrevents unnecessary LLM calls downstream.\n",
        "height": 672,
        "width": 624
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -592,
        -192
      ],
      "id": "832c34f4-c71d-460b-af84-9910e08077e1",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Post Generation & Character Count Validation Loop\n\nLLM generates the post → Code node checks if post is under 500 characters (Telegram caption limit).\n\n**Pass:** Routes to image generation pipeline.\n**Fail:** Feeds back to LLM with the previous output and instruction to shorten, then re-validates. Loops until within limit.",
        "height": 672,
        "width": 848
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        272,
        -160
      ],
      "id": "a24ff707-d7fc-4cc0-8c5c-0716a77715dc",
      "name": "Sticky Note1"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Brand-Consistent Image Compositing\n\nHTML/CSS template with fixed logo (top-right) and dynamic title (lower-middle) → sent to htmlcsstoimage.com API (hcti.io) → returns rendered 1080×1080 PNG → downloaded as binary for Telegram.\n\nLogo position and layout are locked in CSS. Only the title text changes per run, ensuring pixel-perfect structural consistency across all posts.",
        "height": 592,
        "width": 656
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1360,
        -224
      ],
      "id": "46e615e2-ca43-456d-82b0-ef66ba918537",
      "name": "Sticky Note2"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) — Approval Gate\n\nGenerated image card + post sent to user via Telegram for review. Workflow pauses using n8n's built-in \"Send and Wait\" mechanism until user responds.\n\n**Approve →** Post is confirmed and queued for scheduled publishing.\n**Decline →** Opens a feedback form where user describes desired changes. Feedback is combined with the previous output and sent back to the LLM for full regeneration. Loop continues until approved.\n\nAll review interactions happen within a single n8n execution — no external state management required.",
        "height": 752,
        "width": 848
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2096,
        -256
      ],
      "id": "b339a9c6-ed71-44ca-a0b4-670be08777c6",
      "name": "Sticky Note3"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Scheduled Publishing — Mock Endpoints\n\nAfter approval, the Wait node pauses execution until the user's scheduled datetime. At the scheduled time, posts are published in parallel to mock Facebook and Instagram endpoints (separate n8n webhook workflows). User receives confirmation on Telegram for each platform.\n\nMock endpoints simulate real API responses with post IDs, proving the publishing handoff works end-to-end.",
        "height": 592,
        "width": 704
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        3024,
        -208
